#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:15
msgid "Peasant"
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Peasants live in the small hamlets and villages scatt\n"
"ered across the Wesnoth countryside."
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:26
msgid "Village Elder"
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:28
msgid "Each of the villages scattered across the Wesnoth countryside is normally guided by a group of elders, who are the village's wisest and most experienced residents."
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:36
msgid "Senior Village Elder"
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:39
msgid "The entire village looks to the senior elder for guidance.  Strong and wise, the senior elders take responsibility for the community's well-being on their shoulders.  Provincial officials tend to choose senior village elders as magistrates so that legal and customary authority will coincide."
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:51
msgid "Peasant Youth"
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:55
msgid "The scruffy-haired peasant youth are much like the young people living elsewhere in Wesnoth: reckless, cocky, and eager to explore."
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:57
msgid "club"
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:61
msgid "female^Peasant Youth"
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:70
msgid "Night Watchman"
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:74
msgid "The night watchmen are men and women who protect the villages from marauders, both human and otherwise, that prowl the Wesnoth countryside at night."
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:76
msgid "female^Night Watchman"
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:85
msgid "Night Patrolman"
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:88
msgid "Each village has a group of highly capable fighters dedicated to fending off orc raids.  Some of these join the Wesnoth army, while others join the core of the village's night patrol."
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:90
msgid "female^Night Patroller"
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:104
msgid "Peasant Hunter"
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:106
msgid "Villages, especially in wilder areas near frontiers, rely on hunters to bring in much of their food supply.  Their stealth and intimate knowledge of local terrain can be valuable assets in combat."
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:114
msgid "Peasant Trapper"
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:120
msgid ""
"Trappers are skilled hunters who supply food and furs\n"
" for several villages. Their hunting experience makes them most valuable at nig\n"
"ht and in forests and swamps."
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:127
msgid "Peasant Huntsman"
msgstr ""

#: data/campaigns/Liberty/units/Villagers.cfg:130
msgid "Huntsmen have spent their lives in the backwoods and swamps of their wilderness homes.  They can bullseye wamprats and track anything that moves in their territory.  They are highly skilled at hunting at night."
msgstr ""

